            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pork is cooking, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim and slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>finely</p><p>Wash then cut the<strong> pak choi </strong>in half, separating the <strong>white base</strong> and <strong>green tops</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the <strong>white bases</strong> into bite-size pieces and shred the <strong>green tops</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/796.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/796.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/796.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/796.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
