          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/796.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the cooked <strong>pak choi</strong> to a separate bowl</p><p>Return the pan (no need to wash it!) to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sesame seeds</strong> then crack the <strong>eggs</strong> into the pan, over the sesame seeds</p><p>Cook, covered, for 2-3 min or until done to your liking – these are your <strong>sesame fried eggs</strong></p><p>Tip: Give your eggs a little shake before you crack for perfectly centred yolks!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/796.-step-7-x200.jpg",
